## README.md
headings: # BuildingAgent | ## Current focus | ## Key constraints | ## Documentation index
early bullets: - Define the product requirements and architecture. || - Create the monorepo folder structure. || - Document Web, CLI, Email, WhatsApp, runtime, memory, tool, skill, model, and access-control specifications. || - Reserve placeholder files for future building-domain tools and skills. || - Preserve a clear license attribution path for any future Hermes-derived code. || - The local Hermes reference repository is read-only: `/mnt/d/Git_project/references/hermes-agent`. || - Do not vendor the full Hermes repository into BuildingAgent. || - Do not use Streamlit for the Web UI.
chars 1855
## docs/PRODUCT_ARCHITECTURE.md
headings: # Product Architecture | ## Overview | ## Architecture Diagram | ## Boundaries | ## M001 Architecture Output
early bullets: - Entry points authenticate users but do not execute tools directly. || - Runtime receives a resolved request context. || - Tool dispatcher is the only path to tool execution. || - Permission checks are backend-side. || - Memory and data retrieval are project-scoped. || - Audit logs are emitted for sensitive tool, memory, and data access.
chars 1820
